[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hahn-Banach is now proved over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span>, and a couple of corollaries over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>. I verified that the proofs work just as well over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span>, but I imagine it wouldn't be desirable to copy/paste everything - how'd I approach generalizing them?</p>",
        "id": 203985142,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1594833613
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought about this briefly, but am (very) glad that someone else is doing it!</p>",
        "id": 203985527,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1594833809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's not clear whether it would be more efficient to (A) deduce those <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>-corollaries from the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>-versions of the corollaries of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>-Hahn-Banach, or (B) deduce them from your <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>-version of Hahn-Banach</p>",
        "id": 203985699,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1594833881
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What do you think?</p>",
        "id": 203985727,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1594833895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By the way, something I was wondering is whether part of the work can be done for any extension field of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>, and not just for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>?</p>",
        "id": 203985842,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1594833948
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also -- could you also carry out over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span> the isometric inclusion of a normed space in its double dual?  That is the motivation for the corollaries.</p>",
        "id": 203986217,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1594834102
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In the Langlands program we sometimes work over R-bar, an algebraic closure of R with no fixed choice of sqrt (-1)</p>",
        "id": 203989910,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594835817
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what is this object?</p>",
        "id": 203990179,
        "sender_full_name": "Jalex Stark",
        "timestamp": 1594835970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just <code>complex</code> but without choosing <code>I</code></p>",
        "id": 203990220,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1594835990
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what does \"choose\" mean?</p>",
        "id": 203990244,
        "sender_full_name": "Jalex Stark",
        "timestamp": 1594836000
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>complex</code> has a distinguished generator, or equivalently orientation, by it's construction</p>",
        "id": 203990359,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1594836038
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Somehow <code>I</code> is a bit more special than <code>-I</code></p>",
        "id": 203990414,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1594836064
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Kevin is talking about a version where you cannot call one of them more special than the other.</p>",
        "id": 203990457,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1594836082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>gotcha</p>",
        "id": 203990464,
        "sender_full_name": "Jalex Stark",
        "timestamp": 1594836085
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The two square roots of -1 just don't have names, in some sense they are indistinguishable</p>",
        "id": 203990520,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836113
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the whole theory is modded out by swapping the square roots</p>",
        "id": 203990527,
        "sender_full_name": "Jalex Stark",
        "timestamp": 1594836118
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so geometrically it's like a halfspace?</p>",
        "id": 203990749,
        "sender_full_name": "Jalex Stark",
        "timestamp": 1594836212
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's isomorphic to C but in two ways</p>",
        "id": 203990804,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The roots are distinct but nobody chose one to make it special</p>",
        "id": 203990907,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>When you're arguing functorially it's sometimes important</p>",
        "id": 203990964,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836303
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or perhaps psychologically useful, I'm not sure</p>",
        "id": 203991012,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i am happy to believe that even though i can't fill in the details</p>",
        "id": 203991038,
        "sender_full_name": "Jalex Stark",
        "timestamp": 1594836336
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can imagine a category with two objects and an isomorphism between them</p>",
        "id": 203991144,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836370
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And then you make a diagram with a copy of the complex numbers on each object and make the isomorphism be complex conjugation and then you take the limit of the diagram</p>",
        "id": 203991274,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1594836431
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(and then carefully erase from your memory the \"names\" of the two objects in that category that you had to give them when you summoned them from the void...)</p>",
        "id": 204042663,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1594872258
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/203985699\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think it's not clear whether it would be more efficient to (A) deduce those <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>-corollaries from the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>-versions of the corollaries of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>-Hahn-Banach, or (B) deduce them from your <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>-version of Hahn-Banach</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(B) seems easier; just replacing <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\R \\to \\mathbb C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span> in the proofs works out fine. Wondering how to do it without copy/pasting though; I'm guessing defining some sort of \"Hahn-Banach holds over this field\" property?</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/203985842\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>By the way, something I was wondering is whether part of the work can be done for any extension field of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>, and not just for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>No idea :)</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/203986217\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also -- could you also carry out over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span> the isometric inclusion of a normed space in its double dual?  That is the motivation for the corollaries.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Something in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/compare/complex-hahn-banach-corollaries\">this direction</a>? (Pretty rough proof - I've only convinced Lean it's true, not understood it.)</p>",
        "id": 204288636,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1595056246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/203989910\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In the Langlands program we sometimes work over R-bar, an algebraic closure of R with no fixed choice of sqrt (-1)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Is there anything in mathlib about this?</p>",
        "id": 204288638,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1595056262
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Mathlib only has C. Once it has algebraic closures one will be able to prove things about R-bar though. But R-bar and C are isomorphic, it's not a mysterious new object, it's just a different way of thinking about an old object. It's like comparing an n-dimensional vector space with R^n. Sometimes the different point of view can help. It might just be psychological. Whenever I see an R-bar I can choose an isomorphism with C. Sometimes it's best not to though, like sometimes you don't need to choose a basis of V.</p>",
        "id": 204291960,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1595062260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"260507\">@Heather Macbeth</span>  I didn't notice you'd already done the inclusion in the double dual  in <code>dual.lean</code>; will take a look at some point</p>",
        "id": 204292028,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1595062382
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But not over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>, so you should add that!</p>",
        "id": 204302725,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1595082773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"307953\">Ruben Van de Velde</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/204288636\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Wondering how to do it without copy/pasting though; I'm guessing defining some sort of \"Hahn-Banach holds over this field\" property?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Having looked at your branch and seen how directly the proofs adapt, this seems like the right answer!</p>",
        "id": 204304215,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1595085254
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"307953\">Ruben Van de Velde</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/204288636\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Hahn-Banach.20corollaries/near/203985842\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>By the way, something I was wondering is whether part of the work can be done for any extension field of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>, and not just for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span></span></span></span>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>No idea :)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>But the point I am making here is that maybe we already have a \"Hahn-Banach holds over this field\" property, and that property is \"is a (finite?) extension field of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>\".</p>",
        "id": 204304358,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1595085504
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>or (perhaps easier given the available lemmas) \"is a (finite?) algebra over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span></span>\".  By the way, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"214703\">@Yury G. Kudryashov</span> , have you seen this discussion?</p>",
        "id": 204304454,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1595085696
    }
]